who is your favorite hero in literature who is your favorite hero in literature and what is it about him or her that you love what are some of the qualities that make a good hero in a story romanovich raskolnikov from dostoevsky's crime and punishment he was a good man who came up with a bad plan he thought he was ridding the world of evil when he killed a pawn broker but as he came to think more and more on his actions he realized he had committed a murder and a sin and it nearly drove him insane he only regained command of his thoughts and health after he turned himself in to serve his punishment i think he is a strong character who agonized over what to do and then agonized even more over what he had done people both fictional and real are sometimes driven beyond their own capabilities to handle things beyond their control and the choices we make or think we are forced to make have such a huge impact on everyday life what we think is right isn't always so but it's a true man who steps up to the plate and accepts his punishment for wrongs he has done Evil Theory of conduct Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism The Brothers Karamazov Days of our Lives Theodicy Capital punishment Chu-Han contention Alignment (role-playing games) Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Crime fiction Sin Rodion Romanovich Raskolnikov Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Simone Weil Sin City Conspiracy Phoebe Halliwell Summa Theologiae Nihilism Jon Secada Utilitarianism John Howard Yoder Lex Luthor Knots Landing Stock character Legacy of Kain Original sin Dark Phoenix Saga Problem of Hell Fyodor Dostoevsky Crime film Angel Sanctuary Phaedo Nicomachean Ethics Murder Pitaten Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Serial killer Stoicism Fable (video game) Avengers (comics) Justification (theology) Goodness and value theory Baroque chess Merit Satan Psychiatric hospital Suicide Genre fiction Zhao Yun Hell YuYu Hakusho Israel ben Eliezer Joker (comics) Paradise Lost Kain (Legacy of Kai